# SKILL: LLM Fundamentals for Agentic Systems Engineers

> Source: *Building AI Agents with LLMs, RAG, and Knowledge Graphs* — Raieli & Iuculano (Packt, 2025), Chapters 1–3

---

## 1. Text Representation Pipeline

### Encoding Progression
| Method | Captures | Limitation |
|--------|----------|------------|
| One-Hot Encoding | Word presence | No semantics, sparse, huge dimension |
| Bag-of-Words (BoW) | Word frequency | No order, no context |
| TF-IDF | Relative importance | Still no semantics |
| Word2Vec / Embeddings | Semantic meaning | Static (no context-sensitivity) |
| Transformer Embeddings | Contextual meaning | Expensive to compute |

### Key Concepts
- **Tokenization**: Converting text to fundamental units (words, subwords, punctuation)
- **Lemmatization / Stemming**: Normalising word forms before vectorisation
- **Cosine Similarity**: Preferred similarity metric — scale-invariant, bounded [-1, 1], robust to high dimensions
- **Word2Vec**: Self-supervised; trains via context-window binary classification (Skip-gram / CBOW)
- **Embedding dimension sweet spot**: ~300 dimensions (performance plateaus beyond this for Word2Vec)

